<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="2938" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="3.[160,1156,817,1119]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2938">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1843" box="[192,304,817,842]" class="Insecta" family="Sphecidae" genus="Chalybion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2938" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[192,304,817,842]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2938">Chalybion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the most complex and differentiated cocoon among genera of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ashmead" authorityYear="1899" box="[160,300,851,876]" class="Insecta" family="Sphecidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2937" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Sceliphrinae">Sceliphrinae</taxonomicName>
, apparently due to the retention of ancestral traits, as discussed below. 
<bibRefCitation author="Rau P" pageId="3" pageNumber="2938" pagination="62 - 63" refId="ref5355" refString="Rau P. 1915. The differentiation of the cocoons of Pelopoeus caementarius and Chalybion caeruleum (Hymen.). Psyche. 22: 62 - 63. doi: 10.1155 / 1915 / 37374" type="journal article" year="1915">Rau (1915)</bibRefCitation>
commented that cocoons of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="de Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[566,729,886,911]" class="Insecta" family="Sphecidae" genus="Chalybion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2938" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="californicum">
<emphasis box="[566,729,886,911]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2938">C. californicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar to those of 
<emphasis box="[990,1103,886,911]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2938">Sceliphorn</emphasis>
, but have an additional external silken wall, which is a feature not observed in other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ashmead" authorityYear="1899" box="[160,301,955,980]" class="Insecta" family="Sphecidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2937" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Sceliphrinae">Sceliphrinae</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pham PH" box="[316,455,955,980]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2938" pagination="155 - 158" refId="ref5184" refString="Pham PH. 2017. New record of the mud dauber wasp Chalybion malignum (Kohl, 1906) (Hymenoptera: Sphecidae) from Vietnam with the first information on its nesting biology. Punjab Univ J Zool. 32 (1): 155 - 158." type="journal article" year="2017">Pham (2017</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 1d) illustrated a cocoon of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kohl, 1906)" baseAuthorityName="Kohl" baseAuthorityYear="1906" class="Insecta" family="Sphecidae" genus="Chalybion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2938" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malignum">
<emphasis box="[845,1079,955,980]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2938">Chalybion malignum</emphasis>
(Kohl, 1906)
</taxonomicName>
in which the external layer of silk is denser than observed in species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Klug" authorityYear="1801" box="[1037,1150,990,1015]" class="Insecta" family="Sphecidae" genus="Sceliphron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2938" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1037,1150,990,1015]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2938">Sceliphron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ohl M &amp; Hohn P" box="[160,393,1025,1050]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2938" pagination="335 - 348" refId="ref5135" refString="Ohl M, Hohn P. 2011. Taxonomy, bionomics, and ecology of a new species of the blue mud-dauber wasp genus Chalybion from Sulawesi (Hymenoptera, Apoidea). Zoosyst Evol. 87: 335 - 348. doi: 10.1002 / zoos. 201100011" type="journal article" year="2011">Ohl and Höhn (2011</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 4d) provided a photograph of a 
<emphasis box="[823,1038,1025,1050]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2938">Chalibyon sulawesii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ohl M &amp; Hohn P" box="[1047,1155,1025,1050]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2938" pagination="335 - 348" refId="ref5135" refString="Ohl M, Hohn P. 2011. Taxonomy, bionomics, and ecology of a new species of the blue mud-dauber wasp genus Chalybion from Sulawesi (Hymenoptera, Apoidea). Zoosyst Evol. 87: 335 - 348. doi: 10.1002 / zoos. 201100011" type="journal article" year="2011">Ohl, 2011</bibRefCitation>
cocoon in which the meconium can be observed placed in a differentiated, somewhat cylindrical, portion of the cocoon’s basal end.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
